libva-utils
------------------------------------------
libva-utils is a collection of utilities and examples to exercise VA-API in
accordance with the libva project. --enable-tests (default = no) provides a
suite of unit-tests based on Google Test Framework. A driver implementation is
necessary to properly operate.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.1-1
  libgcc1-7.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-7.4.0-1
  libva-drm2-2.4.0-1bl1
  libva-x11_2-2.4.0-1bl1
  libva2-2.4.0-1bl1
  libX11_6-1.6.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.32.0-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://01.org/vaapi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/01org/libva-utils/archive/2.4.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libva-utils-2.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libva-utils-2.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libva-utils-2.4.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libva-utils-2.4.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

